#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2116
msgid ""
"The 3D graphic displays the sensor tilted as per the :ref:`Aberration "
"Inspector Results <ekos-focus-aberration-inspector-results>`.  To help "
"visualise the Petzval surface (see `Petzval Field Curvature "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petzval_field_curvature>`__ for more details)"
" of light coming out of the telescope and incident on the sensor the surface"
" is also modelled.  The higher the backfocus error, the more curved the "
"Petzval surface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2118
msgid ""
"The graphic can be zoomed and rotated using gestures. To zoom use pinch. To "
"rotate use touch-and-move."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2120
msgid ""
"The graphic has a Simulation Mode that allows backfocus and tilt to be "
"adjusted by the sliders. The effect on the sensor's tilt and Petzval surface"
" is displayed in the graphic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2122
msgid "The following options are available for the graphic:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2124
msgid "``Selection``: The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2126
msgid "None: No selection is possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2128
msgid "Item: A datapoint may be selected and data values are displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2130
msgid "Slice: A 2D slice through the 3D graphic is displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2132
msgid "``Theme``: A number of colour themes are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2134
msgid "``Labels``: Checkbox to show / hide tile labels on the graphic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2137
msgid "``Sensor``: Checkbox to show / hide the sensor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2139
msgid ""
"``Petzval Wire``: Checkbox to show / hide the Petzval surface as a graphic "
"wire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2142
msgid "``Petzval Surface``: Checkbox to show / hide the Petzval surface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2145
msgid ""
"``Sim Mode``: Checkbox to toggle Simulation Mode on / off. When off, the "
"graphic displays the sensor and Petzval surface based on the calculated "
"results of the Aberration Inspector run. When on, the sliders for Backfocus,"
" Left-to-Right tilt and Top-to-Bottom tilt are activated, and these can be "
"dragged by the user to adjust the graphic. Hover the mouse over each slider "
"to see the tooltips describing what each slider does."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_manual/ekos-focus.rst:2147
msgid ""
"The 3D graphic is not essential to using Aberration Inspector. All relevant "
"information is displayed in the :ref:`Table <ekos-focus-aberration-"
"inspector-table>` and :ref:`Results <ekos-focus-aberration-inspector-"
"results>` sections of the dialog. Its purpose is to aid the user in "
"understanding Aberration Inspector and to orient themselves with the "
"information the tool provides."
msgstr ""
